The paper deals with privacy-preserving techniques for statistical data analysis, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) and database (cs.DB) communities. The use of histograms and other statistical techniques suggests a focus on data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the use of randomized techniques and approximation algorithms suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
